  "text": "These data demonstrate that enhanced TGF-β signaling particularly in HMEC is considered anti-oncogenic by suppressing oncogene-induced transformation. However, these effects are associated with a higher migration and invasion potential in senescent HMEC which is accompanied by downregulated Rac1b and upregulated Rac1 expression. Together with additional signals mediated by elevated fibrosis/necroptosis and damage-associated molecular patterns, these events can contribute to aging-related breast cancer development [CITATION_1] .",
